Explicator is a planning tool to keep track of all your projects based on priority and dependancy.
It uses the basics of a network planning.

The application is written in Python with PyCharm (http://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/)
Visualisation  of the graph is done with a modified version of XDot (http://code.google.com/p/jrfonseca/wiki/XDot)
User interface is made in PyGTK (http://www.pygtk.org/)

